DataPoint - Class in it.unipi.cc.toretto.kmeans.DTO
In this Kmeans algorithm implementation the DataPoint Class represents a 'point' or a 'datapoint' (we used these words interchangeably) , so every datapoint Object is characterized by two fields 1) coordinates : holds the geometric coordinates of a datapoint 2) data: that holds the weight of a datapoint.
DataPoint() - Constructor for class it.unipi.cc.toretto.kmeans.DTO.DataPoint
Default constructor Initializes 'coordinates' field to an empty arrayList AND the 'data' field to 1
